diff --git a/CONTRIBUTING.md b/CONTRIBUTING.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..5d33325
--- /dev/null
+++ b/CONTRIBUTING.md
@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@
+# Contributing
+
+This repository is a controlled product prototype. Changes must preserve the product, evidence, security, and governance contracts in `product/`.
+
+## Change process
+
+1. Start from a GitHub issue or record the governing decision in the pull request.
+2. Work on a focused branch; do not combine unrelated legal-content, product, and infrastructure changes.
+3. Run the applicable validation locally.
+4. Open a pull request using the repository template.
+5. Resolve review comments and identify any downstream revalidation impact.
+6. Merge only after required checks and owner review pass.
+
+## Validation
+
+```bash
+npm test          # deterministic build + structural, data, and semantic contracts
+npm run qa        # responsive browser and interaction acceptance suite
+npm run verify    # both suites
+```
+
+## Required practices
+
+- preserve source, rule, enterprise fact, deterministic result, and counsel-judgment distinctions
+- identify primary authority, effective date, review date, and uncertainty for legal-content changes
+- keep enterprise data explicitly illustrative unless connected to an approved, permissioned source
+- add or update tests for routes, data contracts, calculations, and interactions
+- maintain keyboard, responsive, reduced-motion, and accessible semantics
+- do not introduce fabricated customer proof or unsupported claims
+- update product contracts or ADRs when architecture changes
+- identify sources, findings, controls, evidence, and decision records requiring revalidation
+- do not commit secrets, private employee or customer data, privileged material, or production work product
+
+## Generated output
+
+`docs/` is committed deployment output. Changes to `src/`, data, or the build must regenerate `docs/` in the same pull request. Do not hand-edit generated pages unless the build system is being repaired and the source-of-truth change is included.
diff --git a/DELIVERABLES.md b/DELIVERABLES.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..ef9c249
--- /dev/null
+++ b/DELIVERABLES.md
@@ -0,0 +1,42 @@
+# Repository contents
+
+## Executable prototype
+
+- `src/` — editable page modules, data, CSS, JavaScript, and SVG icon system
+- `build.js` — deterministic static build
+- `docs/` — generated deployment output
+- `tests/` — structural, data, semantic, responsive, browser, and interaction checks
+- `scripts/` — local rendering and self-contained-preview utilities
+
+## Product and production specification
+
+- `product/PRODUCT-THESIS.md`
+- `product/EXPERIENCE-ARCHITECTURE.md`
+- `product/DATA-MODEL.md`
+- `product/PRODUCTION-ARCHITECTURE.md`
+- `product/VISUAL-SYSTEM.md`
+- `product/CONTENT-DESIGN.md`
+- `product/GOVERNANCE.md`
+- `product/SECURITY-PRIVACY.md`
+- `product/ANALYTICS.md`
+- `product/MIGRATION.md`
+- `product/IMPLEMENTATION-ROADMAP.md`
+- `product/ACCEPTANCE-CRITERIA.md`
+- `product/REPO-AUDIT.md`
+- `product/ADRS/`
+- `product/schemas/legal-intelligence-graph.schema.json`
+
+## GitHub governance and automation
+
+- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — deterministic and browser acceptance tests
+- `.github/workflows/pages.yml` — review-only static prototype deployment
+- `.github/CODEOWNERS` — repository ownership
+- `.github/pull_request_template.md` — governed change checklist
+- `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/` — defect, legal-content, and product-engineering intake
+- `.github/dependabot.yml` — GitHub Actions and npm update monitoring
+- `SECURITY.md` — vulnerability and sensitive-data handling policy
+- `GITHUB-OPERATIONS.md` — repository controls, deployment boundary, and release procedure
+
+## Prototype boundary
+
+This repository is a production-fidelity front-end and system specification. All enterprise names, people, portfolio figures, work states, and financial ranges are illustrative. Production legal rules, calculations, authority versions, integrations, security controls, and customer data require validation and implementation under the governance standards in `product/`.
diff --git a/GITHUB-OPERATIONS.md b/GITHUB-OPERATIONS.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..0fcaece
--- /dev/null
+++ b/GITHUB-OPERATIONS.md
@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@
+# GitHub operations
+
+## Repository
+
+- Canonical repository: `karadzhyan/hotel-wage-law-v2`
+- Default branch: `main`
+- Prototype deployment workflow: `.github/workflows/pages.yml` (builds unversioned `docs/` output)
+- Continuous-integration workflow: `.github/workflows/ci.yml`
+
+## Required repository settings
+
+The repository owner should keep the following controls enabled:
+
+1. Require pull requests for material changes after the initial repository bootstrap.
+2. Require the `CI / verify` status check before merge.
+3. Require conversation resolution and prevent branch deletion.
+4. Restrict force pushes and direct writes to `main`.
+5. Enable private vulnerability reporting.
+6. Configure GitHub Pages to use **GitHub Actions** while the review prototype is intentionally public.
+7. Make the repository private before any non-public property, workforce, customer, matter, evidence, or decision data is introduced.
+
+## Deployment boundary
+
+GitHub Pages is suitable only for review of the static prototype. Enterprise routes contain illustrative data and do not provide authentication, persistence, tenant isolation, privilege, or secure evidence storage. They must not be treated as a production deployment.
+
+## Release procedure
+
+1. Open a scoped pull request.
+2. Run `npm run verify` locally.
+3. Confirm the CI workflow passes.
+4. Review legal-content lineage, prototype disclosures, responsive behavior, and accessibility impact.
+5. Merge through GitHub.
+6. Confirm the Pages deployment completes and inspect the deployed routes.
+7. Record any source, rule, finding, control, evidence, or decision records that require revalidation.
